SIMPLE: footman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Footman
<hw>Foot"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Footmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A soldier who
marches and fights on foot; a foot soldier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A man in waiting; a male servant whose duties are to
attend the door, the carriage, the table, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Formerly, a servant who ran in front of his master's
carriage; a runner.</def> <rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A metallic stand with four feet, for keeping
anything warm before a fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A moth of the family
<fam>Lithosid⟦ae⟧</fam>; -- so called from its livery-like
colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Footmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
